  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At one point, they were supposed to come-- they had pogroms in certain cities.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then all the Jewish organizations, the Jewish [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] longshoremen, the [NON-ENGLISH], everyone was organized, and we waited for them and they didn't go far in the city.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They went back the way they came.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But it was in the last year before the war, was already all kinds of actions by the Polish government against the Jewish, like in colleges, they had to sit in a certain-- certain site.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a numurus nullus, and numurus clausus-- numurus was that they weren't accepted at all, in certain-- in certain colleges, or they were accepted, they were very limited.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Since I wanted to go for engineering, but I couldn't go to engineering school in Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "This was my plan.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But it-- the same goes for medicine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It's why many people-- of the Jews who could afford went to Italy, went to France, went to Belgium.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "As a matter, my first wife, which I met in Rome, she went from Bratislava to Rome, and she finished medicine in Italy.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] this is the-- yes, and the-- and this is also was the reason that we had to-- it was a very strong movement, a Zionist movement.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We could agree with all kinds of politics of each movement, but the principle of things, we knew that Poland-- the Jews had no future in Poland.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because of-- they started, also, to boycott the Jewish stores, and all environment became a very much-- of course very much were by the German influence, but people don't need any-- too big complicated reasons to become anti-Semitic or something like that.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
